 with Text Navigation\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-slider/examples/wordpress-slider-with-text-navigation-id33/</a></p>\n<p>I have inspected the code and there doesn\'t seem to be a class I can associate a colour with.</p>\n<p>Would really appreciate your help!</p>\n<p><strong>Answer</strong>:</p>\n<p>In the plugin, step 3, Options tab, Advanced Options, you can enter the following text to the Advanced Options field:</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\">\r\ndata-navbordercolor=&quot;#006666&quot;\r\ndata-navborderhighlightcolor=&quot;#666600&quot;\r\ndata-navthumbtitlecss=&quot;display:block;position:relative;padding:12px;text-align:center;font:italic 16px Georgia,sans-serif,Arial; color:#eee;&quot;\r\ndata-navshowfeaturedarrow=&quot;false&quot;\r\ndata-timercolor=&quot;#666600&quot;\r\n</pre>\n<p>The 1st line will change the background color of the thumbnail navigations.<br />\nThe 2nd line will change the highlight color.<br />\nThe 3rd line can be used to change text size and format.<br />\nThe 4th line is to hide the red arrow.<br />\nThe 5th line is to change the color of the bottom progress line.</p>\n<p>The demo is as following:</p>\n<div style=\"max-width:800px;margin:0 auto;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:0px;padding-bottom:100px;\"><div class=\"wonderpluginslider\" id=\"wonderpluginslider-38\" data-sliderid=\"38\" data-width=\"800\" data-height=\"320\" data-skin=\"textnavigation\" data-navbordercolor=\"#006666\"\ndata-navborderhighlightcolor=\"#666600\"\ndata-navthumbtitlecss=\"display:block;position:relative;padding:12px;text-align:center;font:italic 16px Georgia,sans-serif,Arial; color:#eee;\"\ndata-navshowfeaturedarrow=\"false\"\ndata-timercolor=\"#666600\" data-autoplay=\"true\" data-randomplay=\"false\" data-autoplayvideo=\"false\" data-isresponsive=\"true\" data-fullwidth=\"false\" data-showtext=\"false\" data-showtimer=\"true\" data-showbottomshadow=\"false\" data-navshowpreview=\"false\" da