INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('57', '1', '2014-09-26 09:49:54', '2014-09-26 09:49:54', '<b>The Beginning:</b>\r\n\r\nAIMS is a great success story by any measure. The company’s history has been more than 12 years in the making—relatively short, but quite impacting.\r\n\r\nInitially called Arab Institute for Marketing and Sales, AIMS was formally established in 2001 when Dr. Yousuf Al Huzaim launched the company focusing on Sales and Marketing, with an aim to provide a unique way of doing business with clients, by being a professional, dynamic, and focused entity with one thing in mind; provision of best practice solutions.\r\n\r\n<b>The </b><b>boom:</b>\r\n\r\nIn 2004, AIMS scored very important contracts with the Saudi Commission for Tourism and Antiquities and with the HRDF, Human Resources Development Fund, This particular project was enormous by any measure, AIMS was to oversee 160 Training &amp; Development Centers all over the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, its objective is to train a 60,000 individual, and making sure they are fit and ready to enter the professional market.\r\n\r\nMajor success of this project and the strategic partnerships formed between AIMS and global companies such as Profiles International and DEI Management Group, put AIMS in a very prominent position in the market, not only for the training, but for management consultation and assessment as well.\r\n\r\n<b>A </b><b>new Name, A new Direction:</b>\r\n\r\nBy 2008, and with AIMS looking to capitalize on rapid successes, Arab Institute for Marketing and Sales for Training became simply AIMS Training and Consultations. The firm has new leadership Mr. Yousuf A. Albuthi and Mr Nader Bechini possessing strong experience in the Human Development and Business Management fields. They shortly transformed the way AIMS does business. By focusing on total training and human development solutions, by instilling customer special care measurements, changing AIMS image and corporate identity, with new vision and values and by expanding AIMS horizons to be the best there is in the region.\r\n\r\nAs a result of his efforts, AIMS clientele now has grown to include some of the major leaders in the Telecom, Industrial, and Trade sectors.\r\n\r\n<b>Where </b><b>we are now:</b>\r\n\r\nBy the end of 2012, AIMS has trained more than 73,000 people. Conducted 75,000 training days, delivered more than 2,400 training courses, and assessed more than 40,000 individuals. Impressive numbers by all measures, given the relatively short time in the market.', 'Our History', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'our-history', '', '', '2014-09-26 09:49:54', '2014-09-26 09:49:54', '', '0', 'http://localhost/aims/?page_id=57', '0', 'page', '', '0');
