INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('69', '1', '2014-09-26 09:54:14', '2014-09-26 09:54:14', '<b>When time is money we  deliver results.</b> Many companies spend a good fortune on training to increase productivity, enhance employee retention and reduce waste. Of course, they want to make sure that the return on investment on training pays off. Training should be measurable in order to determine effective ROI. But many of these program fail to achieve the expected results due to their inadequacy with industry specificities or regional culture.\r\n\r\nAt AIMS we do not subscribe to, nor do we entertain developed-market training concepts. They may work ‘over there’ but they won’t work ‘over here’. All our training contents are customized to our customer needs. We recognize and respect the subtle nuances of how people from diverse industry/backgrounds respond to training.\r\n\r\nWe call ourselves <b>a people partner</b>.  Which means that we work with clients on anything that impacts their people collectively (the organizational culture), through to individually  (often via executive coaching)…and much in between. So if we were being asked what we do, we don’t just do training but we consult, coach and train. The process of engineering high performing cultures is a complex one which is why “tick box” off the shelf solutions are not our style-because they really don’t work very well. Through a rigorous process of consultative discovery, we will partner with our clients and go “under the skin”, to create the right program for their specific organizational needs\r\n\r\nWe also believe that no training program should be viewed as an individual event, but as a process and a journey. We therefore build into each program, a series of follow-up steps, with both managers and front line employees. Follow-Through is essential. We insist upon it. It ensures that results start to emerge early and you get the opportunity to measure it.\r\n\r\nHowever, the most important questions for HR professionals: Once they have selected and implemented a performance development program, how they you know it worked? How they measure the impact of the program ? How they can be sure their employees being assessed and trained have changed their attitude or learned anything, and more importantly, how do you know if they will use what they\'ve learned on the job? AIMS exists to make sure they don’t forget all these and to help them in the measurement process.\r\n\r\nWe focus on guiding leaders, managers and all business professionals to increase their own vitality and, via them, the vitality of their organizations. Our core contribution to this end lies in the mastery of behavior and its conditions. In other words, human interaction and performance. And we are convinced that the future belongs to those businesses who deeply integrate so-called ‘soft’ imperatives (health) with ‘hard’ imperatives (wealth).\r\n\r\n<i>We focus on guiding leaders, managers and all business professionals to increase their own vitality and, via them, the vitality of their organizations</i>', 'We Deliver Results', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'we-deliver-results', '', '', '2014-11-06 09:27:26', '2014-11-06 09:27:26', '', '0', 'http://localhost/aims/?page_id=69', '0', 'page', '', '0');
